Nit: should we unify the prefix of configs that means "enable something", "close something", "disable something", etc.  
IIUC, the unified naming strategy would help end-users to use our system more easily.
Considering that we have already lots of configs starting with "enable_", I'd suggest renaming `close_join_reorder` to `enable_join_reorder`. WDYT?
